Joseph Moreno R Notebook

Hello! The dataset I decided to use is The Complete Pokemon Dataset, taken from Kaggle. This dataset contains all information of the names, types, abilities, stats, and other factors pertaining to each Pokemon from generation 1-7. Due to my interest in Pokemon since childhood, I thought this would be a fun dataset to experiment with and take a more exploratory approach to in regard to analysis. Questions that I wanted to answer through analysis and visualization are present throughout the notebook but some examples include: How many Pokemon are introduced within each generation? Which Pokemon primary type has the best/worst mean stats (combination of defense, attack, speed, special defense, and special attack)? How many grass types (my favorite type) are introduced in each generation?

Dataset link: https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/rounakbanik/pokemon

#group and summarize by type to see the mean base total stats for each pokemon type, effectively seeing which pokemon types have the best and worst stats 
pokemon_df %>%
  group_by(type1) %>%
  summarize(
    mean_stats = mean(base_total),
    sd_stats = sd(base_total)
  )
categories <- c("Bug", "Dark", "Dragon", "Electric", "Fairy", "Fighting", "Fire", "Flying", "Ghost", "Grass", "Ground", "Ice", "Normal", "Poison", "Phychic", "Rock", "Steel", "Water")
counts <- c(380, 449, 522, 436, 427, 414, 450, 453, 434, 412, 426, 433, 401, 399, 461, 447, 491, 426)

summarized_data <- data.frame(Category = categories, Count = counts)

pie_chart <- ggplot(data = summarized_data, aes(x = "", y = "Count", fill = Category)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity") +
  coord_polar("y", start = 0)

pie_chart +
  labs(title = "Pokemon Type1 Stats") +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(legend.position = "bottom")


mean_stats_type1 <- aggregate (pokemon_df$base_total, by=list(type1=pokemon_df$type1), FUN=mean)
sorted_mean_stats_type1 <- mean_stats_type1[order(mean_stats_type1$x),]
mean_stats_type1_graph = barplot(height=sorted_mean_stats_type1$x, names.arg = sorted_mean_stats_type1$type1, col="black", main="Mean Pokemon Type1 Stats", las=2)


#Which pokemon type has the highest/lowest mean value for each of the pokemon stats? 
pokemon_df %>%

  summarize(
    mean_speed = mean(speed),
    mean_attack = mean(attack),
    mean_defense = mean(defense),

    mean_special_defense = mean(sp_defense)
  )
pokemon_count = count(pokemon_df, type1)
